{# MLAT (Mutual Legal Assistance Treaty) request boilerplate.

   Used when the perpetrator's funds have landed at an exchange in a
   country with which the United States has an MLAT. Drafted as a
   STARTING POINT for the AUSA / DOJ Office of International Affairs —
   the operator MUST review jurisdictional specifics + cite the
   relevant treaty article before sending.

   Required Jinja context:
     - case_id, generated_at (UTC ISO)
     - victim: dict with name, jurisdiction
     - perpetrator: dict with destination_country (free-form),
       exchange_name, deposit_address, total_received_usd
     - investigator: dict with name, organization, email
     - tx_evidence: list of {tx_hash, block_time, amount_usd,
       explorer_url}
#}<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>MLAT Request Draft — Case {{ case_id }}</title>
{% include "_styles.html.j2" %}
</head>
<body>

<section class="cover">
  <div class="cover-letterhead">
    <div class="cover-wordmark">
      Recupero
      <span class="tagline">Investigation Services</span>
    </div>
    <div class="cover-letterhead-right">
      <div class="confidential">DRAFT — For AUSA / DOJ-OIA Review</div>
      <div class="date">{{ generated_at }} UTC</div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="cover-title-block">
    <div class="cover-eyebrow">Mutual Legal Assistance Treaty Request — Draft</div>
    <h1>MLAT Request<br/>Boilerplate</h1>
    <p class="cover-subtitle">
      Draft starting point for a request directed to the central
      authority of {{ perpetrator.destination_country }}. This document
      is for INVESTIGATOR USE — DOJ Office of International Affairs
      (OIA) is the issuing authority and must be the sender on the
      final transmission.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="content">

<h2>1. Identification of the Requesting Authority</h2>
<p>
This request is submitted on behalf of investigative counsel
for {{ victim.name }}, a {{ victim.jurisdiction }} resident, in
connection with an ongoing on-chain investigation into the theft
of digital assets. The final request shall be issued by the
Office of International Affairs, U.S. Department of Justice,
to the central authority of {{ perpetrator.destination_country }}.
</p>

<h2>2. Statement of the Offence Being Investigated</h2>
<p>
On {{ incident_date }}, {{ victim.name }} was the victim of
{{ incident_type }}, in which approximately
{{ total_loss_usd }} in digital assets were misappropriated from
the victim's wallet. The underlying criminal conduct is
prosecutable in the United States under one or more of the
following statutes:
</p>
<ul>
  <li>18 U.S.C. § 1343 — Wire Fraud</li>
  <li>18 U.S.C. § 1957 — Engaging in Monetary Transactions in Property Derived from Specified Unlawful Activity</li>
  <li>18 U.S.C. § 1956 — Laundering of Monetary Instruments</li>
  <li>18 U.S.C. § 1030 — Computer Fraud and Abuse (where unauthorized access is alleged)</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>[OPERATOR ACTION: confirm which statutes apply and remove the others.]</strong></p>

<h2>3. Nexus to the Requested Jurisdiction</h2>
<p>
Tracing of the misappropriated funds, conducted using
chain-of-custody-preserved on-chain analysis, established
that a portion of the stolen proceeds were deposited at
<strong>{{ perpetrator.exchange_name }}</strong>, a virtual
asset service provider headquartered in
{{ perpetrator.destination_country }}, in the amount of
<strong>{{ perpetrator.total_received_usd }} USD-equivalent</strong>.
The specific receiving address(es) are:
</p>
{% if perpetrator.deposit_addresses %}
{% for addr in perpetrator.deposit_addresses %}<p class="mono">{{ addr }}</p>
{% endfor %}
{% else %}<p class="mono">{{ perpetrator.deposit_address }}</p>{% endif %}

<h2>4. Investigative Assistance Requested</h2>
<p>Pursuant to the applicable treaty between the United States and
{{ perpetrator.destination_country }} for mutual assistance in
criminal matters, we respectfully request the following:</p>
<ol>
  <li>
    <strong>Account identification:</strong> the identity of the
    {{ perpetrator.exchange_name }} customer associated with the
    receiving address above, including all Know-Your-Customer
    documentation on file (full legal name, date of birth, residence
    address, government-issued identification copies, source-of-funds
    declarations).
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Transaction history:</strong> the complete on-platform
    transaction history for the identified account from the date of
    first deposit through the date of receipt of this request,
    including all deposits, withdrawals (specifying any subsequent
    on-chain transfers and their destination addresses), and internal
    transfers between {{ perpetrator.exchange_name }}-controlled
    accounts.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Asset freeze:</strong> to the extent permitted under
    {{ perpetrator.destination_country }} law, immediate placement
    of an administrative freeze on any remaining balance held in
    the identified customer account, with notification provided to
    the requesting authority within {{ freeze_window_days|default(7) }}
    business days.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>IP and login records:</strong> all logged IP addresses
    used to access the account, all device fingerprints recorded by
    {{ perpetrator.exchange_name }}'s anti-fraud systems, and any
    timestamps thereof.
  </li>
</ol>

<h2>5. Evidence Supplied with This Request</h2>
<p>
The following on-chain transaction records, each independently
verifiable on the public blockchain, constitute the evidentiary
basis for the funds-flow tracing summarized above:
</p>
<table>
  <thead>
    <tr><th>Tx Hash</th><th>Block Time (UTC)</th><th>USD Amount</th><th>Explorer URL</th></tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
  {% for tx in tx_evidence %}
    <tr>
      <td class="mono">{{ tx.tx_hash }}</td>
      <td>{{ tx.block_time }}</td>
      <td>{{ tx.amount_usd }}</td>
      <td>{% if tx.explorer_url %}<a href="{{ tx.explorer_url|safe_url }}">{{ tx.explorer_url }}</a>{% else %}—{% endif %}</td>
    </tr>
  {% endfor %}
  </tbody>
</table>

<h2>6. Confidentiality</h2>
<p>
This request is submitted on a confidential basis. Disclosure to
the customer account holder identified herein prior to U.S.
authorities completing follow-on investigative steps may
significantly compromise the integrity of the underlying
investigation and is therefore respectfully prohibited.
</p>

<h2>7. Point of Contact</h2>
<p>
{{ investigator.name }}<br/>
{{ investigator.organization }}<br/>
{{ investigator.email }}
</p>
<p><em>For routing through DOJ-OIA. The final request shall be
signed and transmitted by the U.S. Department of Justice.</em></p>

</section>
</body>
</html>
